          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Asset finance is any form of lending used to acquire physical business assets — vehicles, machinery, equipment, technology, fit-outs, and more. Rather than paying the full cost upfront from cash reserves, you spread the cost over the useful life of the asset through regular repayments. The asset itself typically serves as security for the finance, keeping rates competitive.</p>
