          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The key advantage of asset finance over using cash is preserving working capital. A business that spends $100,000 cash on a new machine has $100,000 less available for payroll, inventory, marketing, and other operating expenses. The same business using asset finance keeps that $100,000 available while making manageable monthly repayments — and potentially claiming tax deductions on the interest, depreciation, and GST.</p>
